						<summary>

						<p>Slab built into the floor of the cow-shed in a private house called ‘chitpāḍi-bīḍu.’</p>						

						<p>1493 A.D. (?)</p>						

						<p>This badly damaged worn out record is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1416, Pramādicha, Mēsha 1, Sunday.</hi> The details are irregular, the <hi rend="italic">tithi</hi> corresponding to 1493 A.D., March 27, the weekday being Wednesday. The Śaka year was 1415.</p>						

						<p>It registers a gift of land by a person (name lost) who was the grand daughter's son of Devaru-seṭṭi, for feeding a brahmaṇa probably in the <hi rend="italic">maṭha</hi> attached to the temple of Lakshmīnārāyaṇa at Chiṭṭapāḍi. The details are lost. Cf. No. 582/29-30 above. </p>						

						</summary>
